It belongs to the group referred to as transmissible spongiform encephalopathies (TSEs), or prion diseases, along with bovine spongiform encephalopathy (BSE) in cattle and Creutzfeldt to Jakob disease in humans (reviewed by Prusiner, 1997). The infectious agent responsible for these diseases has been termed a prion, and is thought to be composed entirely of a pathological form (PrPSc) of a host-encoded protein  to  the prion protein (PrPC)
